cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.Distributed, cs.PL, cs.SE. 

This paper focuses on the performance of executing Ethereum smart contracts in parallel, which involves distributed computing and concurrency control. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also relevant due to the nature of smart contracts and their execution. Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a new speculative execution engine for smart contracts.
